        <name>7.3.2.6 Compute a 3x3 determinant</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By expanding along the first row, compute the determinant of the matrix \(A = {@matrixa@}\).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The determinant \(\Delta\) is: [[input:ans1]][[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;For \(A={@matrixa@}\), we have: \begin{align*} a_{11} &amp;amp; = {@matrixa[1,1]@}, &amp;amp; a_{12} &amp;amp; = {@matrixa[1,2]@}, &amp;amp; a_{13} &amp;amp; = {@matrixa[1,3]@}, \\ A_{11} &amp;amp; = \det{{@AA11@}} = {@determinant(AA11)@}, &amp;amp; A_{12} &amp;amp; = \det{{@AA12@}} = {@determinant(AA12)@}, &amp;amp; A_{13} &amp;amp; = \det{{@AA13@}} = {@determinant(AA13)@}. \end{align*}&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Therefore \[\Delta = a_{11}A_{11}+a_{12}A_{12}+a_{13}A_{13} = {@ta1@}.\]&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
